    def before_scenario_browser_setup(self, pobj_scenario, pobj_globaldict, **kwargs):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is the configuration for browser setup

    :param pobj_globaldict:
    :type pobj_globaldict: dict
    :param pobj_scenario: pobj_scenario is the scenario object
    :type pobj_scenario: object
    :param bool_use_grid: bool_use_grid is to specify where the execution should be done(local or selenium grid)
    :type bool_use_grid: boolean
    :param pstr_selenium_grid_ip: pstr_selenium_grid_ip is the ip of selenium grid
    :type pstr_selenium_grid_ip: string
    :param pstr_browser: pstr_browser is the browser name
    :type pstr_browser: string
    :param web_capabilities: web_capabilities accepts a dictionary which has browser configuration for selenium grid
    :type web_capabilities: dictionary

    """
    try:

        bool_use_grid = kwargs.get("pbool_use_grid", False)
        str_selenium_grid_ip = kwargs.get("pstr_selenium_grid_ip", None)
        str_current_browser = kwargs.get("pstr_browser", "chrome")
        dict_capabilities = kwargs.get("web_capabilities", None)
        if dict_capabilities != {} and dict_capabilities is not None:
            if "use_caps" in dict_capabilities:
                if dict_capabilities["use_caps"]:
                    self.logger.debug("Desired Capabilities: ", dict_capabilities)
                else:
                    dict_capabilities = {}
            else:
                dict_capabilities = {}

        str_chrome_options = kwargs.get("pstr_chrome_options", None)
        str_firefox_options = kwargs.get("pstr_firefox_options", None)
        str_edge_options = kwargs.get("pstr_edge_options", None)
        str_ie_options = kwargs.get("pstr_ie_options", None)
        str_safari_options = kwargs.get("pstr_safari_options", None)
        str_firefox_preferences = kwargs.get("pstr_firefox_preferences", None)
        pdict_proxy_options = kwargs.get("pdict_proxy_options", None)
        pbool_ie_edge_clear_browser_hist = kwargs.get("pbool_ie_edge_clear_browser_hist", False)
        dict_custom_experimental_options = kwargs.get("pdict_custom_experimental_options", None)

        if (pytest.datadriven >= pytest.rowcount + 1) or len(
            pobj_scenario.examples.examples
        ) >= pytest.counter:
            if pytest.driver is None:
                pobj_globaldict["obj_wdf"] = WebDriverFactory()
                pobj_globaldict["obj_wdf"].create_driver(
                    bool_use_grid,
                    pstr_selenium_grid_ip=str_selenium_grid_ip,
                    browser=str_current_browser,
                    capabilities=dict_capabilities,
                    plist_chrome_options=str_chrome_options,
                    plist_firefox_options=str_firefox_options,
                    plist_firefox_preferences=str_firefox_preferences,
                    pdict_proxy_options=pdict_proxy_options,
                    plist_edge_options=str_edge_options,
                    pbool_ie_edge_clear_browser_hist=pbool_ie_edge_clear_browser_hist,
                    plist_ie_options=str_ie_options,
                    plist_safari_options=str_safari_options,
                    pdict_custom_experimental_options=dict_custom_experimental_options,
                )
                pytest.driver = pobj_globaldict["obj_wdf"].get_driver()
                pytest.driver.implicitly_wait(ConfigUtils(os.getcwd()).get_implicit_wait())
                pobj_globaldict["obj_wca"] = WebClientActions(pytest.driver)
                pobj_globaldict["obj_kma"] = KeyboardMouseActions(pytest.driver)
                pobj_globaldict["businessutils_mi"] = BusinessUtils_UI_SPG(
                    pobj_globaldict["obj_wca"].driver
                )
                # pobj_globaldict['businessutils_platts'] = PLATTSUISPG(pobj_globaldict['obj_wca'].driver)
        else:
            if pytest.driver is None:
                pobj_globaldict["obj_wdf"] = WebDriverFactory()
                pobj_globaldict["obj_wdf"].create_driver(
                    bool_use_grid,
                    pstr_selenium_grid_ip=str_selenium_grid_ip,

                    plist_safari_options=str_safari_options,
                    pdict_custom_experimental_options=dict_custom_experimental_options,
                )
                pytest.driver = pobj_globaldict["obj_wdf"].get_driver()
                pytest.driver.implicitly_wait(ConfigUtils(os.getcwd()).get_implicit_wait())
                pobj_globaldict["obj_wca"] = WebClientActions(pytest.driver)
                pobj_globaldict["obj_kma"] = KeyboardMouseActions(pytest.driver)

                    pobj_globaldict["obj_wca"].driver

            pytest.obj_driver = pobj_globaldict["obj_wca"]

    """
    Description:
            |  this method is to perform a set of configuration based on scenario tags before a scenario get executes

    :type pobj_feature: object
    :param pobj_scenario: pobj_scenario is the scenario object which would be passed from the hooks

    :param plist_command_args: plist_command_args is the command line input which would be passed from a user
    :type plist_command_args: list
    :param pobj_globaldict: pobj_globaldict is the pytest global dictionary object
    :type pobj_globaldict: object

    """
    try:
        self.logger.info(
            "\nthis will be printed before scenario execution, scenario name:\n {}".format(
                pobj_scenario.name

            pobj_request, pobj_feature, pobj_scenario, pobj_globaldict
        )
        str_chrome_options = None
        str_firefox_options = None
        str_firefox_preferences = None
        str_edge_options = None
        str_ie_options = None
        str_safari_options = None

        bool_ie_edge_clear_browser_hist = False
        dict_custom_experimental_options = None
        if "ui_web" in pobj_scenario.tags and "mobile_web" in pobj_scenario.tags:
            if "chrome_options" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                str_chrome_options = self.config_utils.base_config["chrome_options"]
            if "firefox_options" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                str_firefox_options = self.config_utils.base_config["firefox_options"]
            if "edge_options" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                str_edge_options = self.config_utils.base_config["edge_options"]
            if "ie_options" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                str_ie_options = self.config_utils.base_config["ie_options"]
            if "safari_options" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                str_safari_options = self.config_utils.base_config["safari_options"]
            if "firefox_preferences" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                str_firefox_preferences = self.config_utils.base_config["firefox_preferences"]
            if "use_proxy" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                bool_use_proxy = self.config_utils.base_config.get("use_proxy")
                if bool_use_proxy == True:
                    if "proxy_options" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                        pdict_proxy_options = self.config_utils.base_config["proxy_options"]
            if "ie_edge_clear_browser_history" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                bool_ie_edge_clear_browser_hist = self.config_utils.base_config.get(
                    "ie_edge_clear_browser_history"
                )
            if "custom_experimental_options" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                dict_custom_experimental_options = self.config_utils.base_config.get(
                    "custom_experimental_options"
                )

            bool_run_on_mobile = self.config_utils.fetch_run_on_mobile()
            if bool_run_on_mobile:

            else:

                    pdict_proxy_options=pdict_proxy_options,
                    pstr_edge_options=str_edge_options,

        elif "ui_web" in pobj_scenario.tags:

    try:
        for scenario_name, scenario in pobj_feature.scenarios.items():
            self.kibana_reporting.before_step_auto_dash_configuration(pobj_step)
            if scenario.templated:
                header = scenario.examples.example_params
                values = scenario.examples.examples

            elif "data_driven_keys" in pytest.globalDict.keys():
                header = pytest.globalDict["data_driven_keys"]
                values = pytest.globalDict["data_driven_values"]

            if scenario.templated or "data_driven_keys" in pytest.globalDict.keys():

                step_first = pobj_scenario.steps[0].name
                step_name = pobj_step.name
                current_scenario_name = pobj_scenario.name

                if current_scenario_name == self.scenario_name:
                    if step_first == step_name:
                        if self.count == 0:
                            self.count = self.count + 1
                        else:
                            self.count = self.count + 1
                else:
                    self.count = 0

                n = 0
                for items in header:
                    item = "<" + items + ">"
                    if item in step_name:
                        step_name = step_name.replace(item, values[self.count][n])
                        n = n + 1
                    else:
                        n = n + 1

                pobj_globaldict["step_name"] = step_name
                if scenario.examples.example_params is not None:
                    pobj_globaldict["example_converters"] = scenario.examples.example_params
                self.scenario_name = current_scenario_name

    except Exception as e:
        self.logger.exception("Error in before_step_configuration-->" + str(e))

    """

    @staticmethod
def delete_log_files(abs_log_folder_path):
    """This method deletes the log files after session finished."""
    try:
        files = [
            i
            for i in os.listdir(abs_log_folder_path)
            if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(abs_log_folder_path, i)) and i.startswith("log_")
        ]
        for _file in files:
            log_file_path = os.path.join(abs_log_folder_path, _file)
            if os.path.isfile(log_file_path):
                os.remove(log_file_path)
                print(f"{_file} log file is removed from local: {abs_log_folder_path} ")
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"error occured while deleting the log files in from {abs_log_folder_path}")
        print(str(e))

    def is_parallel_execution(self, plist_argslist):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is to check parallel execution

    :param plist_argslist: plist_argslist is the command line argumens
    :type plist_argslist: list

    :return: boolean
    """
    try:
        pbool_parallel = None
        if "-c" in plist_argslist:
            pbool_parallel = True
        for i in plist_argslist:
            if "-n=" in i:
                pbool_parallel = True
                break
            if "--tests-per-worker" in i:
                pbool_parallel = True
                break
            if "--workers" in i:
                pbool_parallel = True
                break
            if "-n" == i:
                pbool_parallel = True
                break

        return pbool_parallel
    except Exception as e:
        self.logger.exception("Error in is_parallel_execution-->" + str(e))

    def parse_data_table(self, pstr_text, pstr_orient="dict"):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method to parse gherkin command

    :param pstr_text: pstr_text is the gherkin step
    :type pstr_text: String
    :param pstr_orient: pstr_orient is the data type
    :type pstr_orient: String

    """
    try:
        parsed_text = [
            [x.strip() for x in line.split("|")]
            for line in [x.strip().strip("|") for x in pstr_text.splitlines()]
        ]
        header, *data = parsed_text
        if pstr_orient == "dict":
            return [dict(zip(header, line)) for line in data]
        else:
            if pstr_orient == "columns":
                data = [[line[i] for line in data] for i in range(len(header))]
            return header, data
    except Exception as e:
        self.logger.exception("Error in parse_data_table-->" + str(e))

    def pytest_after_scenario_tags_configuration(
    self, pobj_scenario, plist_commandargs, pobj_globaldict, pobj_feature
):
    """
    Description:
        |  this method is to perform a set of configuration based on scenario tags after a scenario get executes

    :param pobj_scenario: pobj_scenario is the scenario object which would be passed from the hooks
    :type pobj_scenario: object
    :param plist_command_args: plist_command_args is the command line arguments  which would be passed from an user as input
    :type plist_command_args: list
    :param pobj_globaldict: pobj_globaldict is the pytest global dictionary object
    :type pobj_globaldict: object

    """
    self.logger.info("\nthis will be printed after scenario \n {}".format(pobj_scenario.name))

    # self.after_scenario_kibana_configuration(pobj_globaldict)

        "local_reporting" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys()
        and (not bool(self.config_utils.base_config["auto_dashboard_report"]))
        and bool(self.config_utils.base_config["local_reporting"])
    ):

        local_reporting.attach_exception_logs()

        self.after_scenario_browser_teardown(pobj_scenario, plist_commandargs, pobj_globaldict)

        plist_commandargs

        self.after_scenario_thick_client_teardown(pobj_scenario, pobj_globaldict)
    if "mobile_web" in pobj_scenario.tags and not self.is_parallel_execution(plist_commandargs):
        self.after_scenario_mobile_teardown()
    if "mobile_ios" in pobj_scenario.tags and not self.is_parallel_execution(plist_commandargs):
        self.after_scenario_mobile_teardown()
        self.logger.info("mobile_iOS configuration")
    if "mobile_android" in pobj_scenario.tags and not self.is_parallel_execution(
        plist_commandargs
    ):
        self.after_scenario_mobile_teardown()
        self.logger.info("mobile_android configuration")

    self.kibana_reporting.pytest_after_scenario_auto_dash_configuration(
        pobj_scenario, pobj_feature
    )

    def read_excel(self, pstr_filename, psheet_reference):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method reads excel file based on the path it gets
    :param pstr_filename: pstr_filename is the name of excel file with the path
    :type pstr_filename: String
    :param psheet_reference: psheet_reference is the name or index of the sheet
    :type psheet_reference: String or int

    :return: List
    """
    try:
        values = []
        headers = []
        warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=PendingDeprecationWarning)
        warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=DeprecationWarning)
        my_file = xlrd.open_workbook(pstr_filename)
        if type(psheet_reference) == str:
            sheet_obj = my_file.sheet_by_name(psheet_reference)
        else:
            sheet_obj = my_file.sheet_by_index(psheet_reference)
        max_row = sheet_obj.nrows
        max_column = sheet_obj.ncols
        for rows in range(1, max_row):
            values_tuple = ()
            for cols in range(0, max_column):
                cell_obj = sheet_obj.cell(rows, cols)
                values_tuple = values_tuple + (cell_obj.value,)
            values.append(values_tuple)
        for cols in range(0, max_column):
            cell_headers = sheet_obj.cell(0, cols)
            headers.append(cell_headers.value)
        pytest.globalDict["data_driven_keys"] = headers
        pytest.globalDict["data_driven_values"] = values
        return values, headers

    except Exception as e:
        self.logger.exception("Error in read_excel method-->" + str(e))

    def read_json_datadriven(self, pstr_filename, pstr_rootkey, pbool_is_datadriven_dir=True):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is to read json file which is in data_driven folder and to return headers and values in the form of list and tuples respectively

    :param pstr_filename: pstr_filename is the name of json file
    :type pstr_filename: String

    :param pstr_rootkey: pstr_rootkey is the root key of json file
    :type pstr_rootkey: String

    :param pbool_is_datadriven_dir: if pbool_is_datadriven_dir is set to true file path would be picked from "testdata/data_driven" folder if not given file path will be picked
    :type pbool_is_datadriven_dir: Boolean

    :return: List,tuple
    Examples:
        |  Format of json should be as shown below
        |  {
        |   "test_data":
        |   [
        |    {
        |     "Tab": "Annotations"
        |    }
        |   ]
        |  }
        |  method should be called as hook_utils.read_json("TestData.json","test_data")
        |  test_data is the rootkey of "TestData.json" file

    """

    try:
        values_tuple = ()
        if pbool_is_datadriven_dir:
            if os.path.exists(
                self.config_utils.get_datadriven_dirpath() + os.sep + pstr_filename
            ):
                str_filename = (
                    self.config_utils.get_datadriven_dirpath() + os.sep + pstr_filename
                )
            else:
                pytest.fail(
                    "Given "
                    + self.config_utils.get_datadriven_dirpath()
                    + os.sep
                    + pstr_filename
                    + " file is not available in specified location"
                )

        else:
            str_filename = pstr_filename

        with open(str_filename) as cred_file:
            parsed_json = json.load(cred_file)
        values_list = parsed_json[pstr_rootkey]
        final_values_list = []
        keys_list = []
        list_length = len(values_list)
        for root_key in values_list:
            for child_key in root_key.keys():
                if child_key not in keys_list:
                    keys_list.append(child_key)
        for values in values_list:
            for l in range(0, list_length):
                values_tuple = ()
                for keys, tuple_values in values.items():
                    values_tuple = values_tuple + (tuple_values,)
            final_values_list.append(values_tuple)
        return keys_list, final_values_list
    except Exception as e:
        self.logger.exception("Error in read_json_datadriven-->" + str(e))

    def session_finish_configuration(self, pobj_session=None, pstr_custom_html=None):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is invoked after the test is finished

    """
    try:
        self.kibana_reporting.session_finish_auto_dash_configuration(pobj_session)
        if pytest.mobile_driver is not None:
            pytest.mobile_driver.quit()
            pytest.mobile_driver = None
            pytest.driver = None
        if "webclient_teardown_flag" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
            if self.config_utils.base_config["webclient_teardown_flag"] is False:
                if pytest.driver is not None:
                    pytest.driver.quit()
                    pytest.driver = None
        if "thickclient_teardown_flag" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
            if self.config_utils.base_config["thickclient_teardown_flag"] is False:
                if ("cts_form_flag") in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                    if self.config_utils.base_config["cts_form_flag"] is False:
                        if pytest.obj_tca is not None:
                            pytest.obj_tca.window.close()
                if pytest.handler is not None:
                    pytest.handler.kill()
                    pytest.handler = None

        custom_html = False
        if os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "master":
            custom_html_data = pstr_custom_html
            if "custom_html_alerts" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                custom_html = self.config_utils.base_config["custom_html_alerts"]
            if pobj_session is not None:
                if "execution_complete" in os.environ:
                    if custom_html:
                        self.__teams_email_alerts(pobj_session, custom_html_data)
                    else:
                        self.__teams_email_alerts(pobj_session)
                    # Handling the bulk upload after the completion of execution

        str_auto_path = self.config_utils.get_auto_export_dirpath()
        auto_exp_files = str_auto_path + "AutoExpo_*" + ".csv"
        list_log_files = glob.glob(str_auto_path + "\\AutoExpo_*" + ".csv")
        for filePath in list_log_files:
            try:
                os.remove(filePath)
            except Exception as e:
                self.logger.exception(
                    f"Error while deleting file:{filePath} and error is {str(e)}"
                )

        failed_count = pobj_session.testsfailed

        if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
            if "rerun_failures_count" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                if (
                    self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures_count"]
                    == self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_iteration"]
                ):
                    config_yaml_re = self.config_utils.base_config
                    config_yaml_re.pop("rerun_iteration")
                    self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml_re)

            if self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures"] and failed_count > 0:
                val = self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures_count_dummy"]
                self.logger.debug(val)
                # if val > int(self.config_utils.base_config['rerun_failures_count']):
                if val <= 0:
                    self.logger.debug(val)
                    if "rerun_failures_count" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                        self.logger.debug(
                            int(self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures_count"])
                        )
                    # pobj_session.config.cache.set("example/value", None)

                    config_yaml_re = self.config_utils.base_config
                    config_yaml_re.pop("rerun_failures_count_dummy")

                    self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml_re)
                else:
                    projectpath = self.config_utils.get_project_path()
                    with open(projectpath + "/" + ".pytest_cache/v/cache/lastfailed", "r") as f:
                        b = f.read()
                        f.close()
                    print(b)
                    print(type(b))
                    d = json.loads(b)
                    up_json = {}
                    for k, v in d.items():
                        if len(k) != 0:
                            up_json[k] = v
                    with open(
                        projectpath + "/" + ".pytest_cache/v/cache/lastfailed", "w+"
                    ) as f1:
                        json.dump(up_json, f1, indent=3)

                    if len(up_json) > 0:
                        self.logger.info("last failed run %d" % val)
                        if "rerun_failures_count_dummy" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                            rerunval1 = self.config_utils.base_config[
                                "rerun_failures_count_dummy"
                            ]
                            config_yaml1 = self.config_utils.base_config
                            config_yaml1["rerun_failures_count_dummy"] = int(rerunval1) - 1
                            if config_yaml1["rerun_iteration"] == "NA":
                                config_yaml1["rerun_iteration"] = 0

                            config_yaml1["rerun_iteration"] = (
                                config_yaml1["rerun_iteration"] + 1
                            )
                            self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml1)
                        update_parent = self.config_utils.base_config
                        self.open_file_with_writemode(update_parent)
                        self.__rerun_last_failed_test()
                        pytest.globalDict.clear()
                    else:
                        pytest.exit("No Failure Log generated")

            if failed_count == 0 or not self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures"]:
                config_yaml_fail = self.config_utils.base_config
                if "rerun_failures_count_dummy" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                    config_yaml_fail.pop("rerun_failures_count_dummy")

                self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml_fail)
        pstr_execution_id = os.environ.get("execution_id")
        if "enable_logging" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
            if self.config_utils.base_config["enable_logging"]:
                if pstr_execution_id not in [None, ""]:
                    self.upload_log_files_after_session_finish()
            abs_log_folder_path = (
                self.config_utils.get_project_path() + os.sep + self.log_folder_path
            )
            if self.file_handler_info:
                self.file_handler_info.close()

    except Exception as e:
        print("Error in session_finish_configuration-->" + str(e))

    def set_nested_item(self, pdict_data, plist_map, pstr_val):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is to update data in config.yml

    :param pdict_data: pstr_session is data of a yaml file
    :type pdict_data: Dictonary

    :param plist_map: plist_map is list of keys
    :type plist_map: plist_map

    :param pstr_val: pstr_val is the value that should be updated.
    :type pstr_val: String
    """
    try:
        functools.reduce(operator.getitem, plist_map[:-1], pdict_data)[plist_map[-1]] = pstr_val
        return pdict_data
    except Exception as e:
        self.logger.exception("Error in set_nested_item-->" + str(e))

    def update_commandline_data(self, pstr_session):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is to update data in config.yml from command line

    :param pstr_session: pstr_session is the session object which would be passed from hooks
    :type pstr_session: object
    """
    try:
        config_yaml = self.config_utils.base_config

        if pstr_session.config.option.mobile_platform is not None:
            config_yaml["mobile_platform"] = pstr_session.config.option.mobile_platform
        if pstr_session.config.option.selenium_grid_ip is not None:
            config_yaml["selenium_grid_ip"] = pstr_session.config.option.selenium_grid_ip
            config_yaml["use_grid"] = True
        if pstr_session.config.option.browser is not None:
            config_yaml["current_execution_browser"] = pstr_session.config.option.browser
        if pstr_session.config.option.chrome_options is not None:
            config_yaml["chrome_options"] = literal_eval(
                pstr_session.config.option.chrome_options
            )
        if pstr_session.config.option.firefox_options is not None:
            config_yaml["firefox_options"] = literal_eval(
                pstr_session.config.option.firefox_options
            )
        if pstr_session.config.option.edge_options is not None:
            config_yaml["edge_options"] = literal_eval(pstr_session.config.option.edge_options)
        if pstr_session.config.option.ie_options is not None:
            config_yaml["ie_options"] = literal_eval(pstr_session.config.option.ie_options)
        if pstr_session.config.option.safari_options is not None:
            config_yaml["safari_options"] = literal_eval(
                pstr_session.config.option.safari_options
            )

        execution_environment = ""
        environment_type = ""
        pytest.globalDict["jenkins_build"] = pstr_session.config.option.jenkins_build

        if pstr_session.config.option.kibana_reporting is not None:
            config_yaml["kibana_reporting"] = pstr_session.config.option.kibana_reporting
            self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml)
        if pstr_session.config.option.auto_dashboard_report is not None:
            if "auto_dashboard_report" in config_yaml.keys():
                if pstr_session.config.option.auto_dashboard_report in ("false", "False"):
                    config_yaml["auto_dashboard_report"] = False
                    self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml)
                elif pstr_session.config.option.auto_dashboard_report in ("true", "True"):
                    config_yaml["auto_dashboard_report"] = True
                    self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml)
        if pstr_session.config.option.config_keys is not None:

            cust_keys = pstr_session.config.option.config_keys
            y = yaml.safe_load(cust_keys)
            key_lst1 = []
            for cu_k, cu_v in y.items():
                if "__" in cu_k:
                    paths = str(cu_k).split("__")
                    key_lst1 = key_lst1 + paths
                    config_yaml = self.set_nested_item(config_yaml, key_lst1, cu_v)
                else:
                    if cu_k not in config_yaml.keys():
                        pytest.fail("Given :" + cu_k + "  is not available in config.yml")
                    else:
                        config_yaml[cu_k] = cu_v
            self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml)
        if (
            (pstr_session.config.option.environment is None)
            and (pstr_session.config.option.environment_type is None)
            and (pstr_session.config.option.execution_environment is None)
        ):
            execution_environment = config_yaml["execution_environment"]
            environment_type = config_yaml["environment_type"]
            base_url = "NA"
            if "base_url" in config_yaml["env"][execution_environment][environment_type].keys():
                base_url = config_yaml["env"][execution_environment][environment_type][
                    "base_url"
                ]
            config_yaml["environment"] = base_url

            if pstr_session.config.option.custom_params is not None:

                cust_keys = pstr_session.config.option.custom_params
                y = yaml.safe_load(cust_keys)
                key_lst = ["env", execution_environment, environment_type]
                for cust_k, cust_v in y.items():
                    if "__" not in cust_k:
                        if (
                            cust_k
                            not in config_yaml["env"][execution_environment][
                                environment_type
                            ].keys()
                        ):
                            pytest.fail(
                                "Given "
                                + cust_k
                                + "is not available under "
                                + execution_environment
                                + "/"
                                + environment_type
                            )
                        else:
                            config_yaml["env"][execution_environment][environment_type][
                                cust_k
                            ] = cust_v
                    else:
                        paths = str(cust_k).split("__")
                        key_lst = key_lst + paths
                        config_yaml = self.set_nested_item(config_yaml, key_lst, cust_v)

            if environment_type not in config_yaml["env"][execution_environment].keys():
                pytest.fail(
                    "Given "
                    + environment_type
                    + " is not available under this"
                    + execution_environment
                )

            if (pstr_session.config.option.default_db_user__username is not None) and (
                pstr_session.config.option.default_db_user__password is not None
            ):
                if (
                    "default_db_user"
                    not in config_yaml["env"][execution_environment][environment_type].keys()
                ):
                    pytest.fail(
                        "Given default_db_user is not available under "
                        + execution_environment
                        + "/"
                        + environment_type
                    )
                config_yaml["env"][execution_environment][environment_type]["default_db_user"][
                    "username"
                ] = pstr_session.config.option.default_db_user__username
                config_yaml["env"][execution_environment][environment_type]["default_db_user"][
                    "password"
                ] = pstr_session.config.option.default_db_user__password

            self.open_file_with_writemode(config_yaml)

        if (
            (pstr_session.config.option.environment is not None)
            and (pstr_session.config.option.environment_type is None)
            and (pstr_session.config.option.execution_environment is None)
        ):
            flag = False
            for keys, values in config_yaml["env"].items():
                for keys1, values1 in config_yaml["env"][keys].items():
                    for keys2, values2 in config_yaml["env"][keys][keys1].items():
                        if (
                            config_yaml["env"][keys][keys1][keys2]
                            == pstr_session.config.option.environment
                        ):
                            execution_environment = keys
                            environment_type = keys1
                            flag = True
                            break
                    if flag:
                        break
                if flag:
                    break
            config_yaml["execution_environment"] = execution_environment

            config_yaml["environment"] = pstr_session.config.option.environment

                y = yaml.safe_load(cust_keys)

                for cust_k, cust_v in y.items():

    def upload_log_files_after_session_finish(
    self,
):
    """
    Description:
        | This method will upload the the log files after sesion finished.

    """
    try:
        print("uploading log files to s3..")
        session = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_aws_session()
        client = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_s3_client(session)
        pstr_execution_id = os.environ.get("execution_id")
        project_path = self.config_utils.get_project_path()
        abs_log_folder_path = project_path + os.sep + self.log_folder_path
        files = [
            i
            for i in os.listdir(abs_log_folder_path)
            if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(abs_log_folder_path, i)) and i.startswith("log_")
        ]
        files.sort()
        parallel_master_log_file = ""
        for _file in files:
            print(f"log file: {_file}")
            local_log_file_path = os.path.join(abs_log_folder_path, _file)
            if "-n" in sys.argv and _file.startswith("log_master"):
                parallel_master_log_file = "master"
            else:
                with open(local_log_file_path, "r") as file:
                    data = file.read()
                if len(str(data)) > 0:
                    try:
                        binary = bytes(data, "utf-8")
                        encoded_data = base64.b64encode(binary)
                        uploaded_file_path = (
                            self.python_client_reporting_utils.save_string_data(
                                client, encoded_data, pstr_execution_id, _file
                            )
                        )
                        print("Transferring complete file {} from Local to s3...".format(_file))
                        print("uploaded log file path-->")
                        print(uploaded_file_path)
                    except Exception as e:
                        print(f"error occured while uploading log file to s3 in-->:{str(e)}")
    except Exception as e:
        print(
            f"error occured after session finish here in upload_log_files_after_session_finish-->:{str(e)}"
        )
